div.div:
Add 'fcm_token' and 'is_fcm' to User model
This commit adds 'fcm_token' and 'is_fcm' fields to the User model. This is to support Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) functionality. 'is_fcm' is cast as a boolean to track if FCM is enabled for each user.

Remove 'auth.api' middleware from ApiController
This commit removes the unnecessary 'auth.api' middleware from the ApiController constructor. From now on, the middleware is not tied to all API routes, providing more flexibility for individual routes' requirements. The 'auth.api' constraint was also removed to ensure more straightforward handling.

Simplify namespace usage in ApiController methods
This commit refactors the ApiController code to use shorter syntax by directly referring to the User class rather than providing the full namespace. This change enhances readability and maintainability of the code.

Add support for Redis aggregate connections and search queries
This update introduces key classes of Redis including 'ACL', 'PredisException' and 'Aggregate', providing enhanced command handling in geospatial search queries and time series. It also broadens the .gitignore file to include vendor and composer.lock files, supporting better version control.

Add new files to geocoder package and update .gitignore
This commit includes addition of several new files to the 'willdurand/geocoder' package. This includes PHP classes like AbstractProvider, Address, AdminLevelCollection, etc. Moreover, entries for 'vendor' and 'composer.lock' are also added to the '.gitignore' of 'alexpechkarev/google-maps' package.
